commit.message:
Modify get tenant names APIs (#4688)

This PR modifies the logic of getting tenant name APIs.

The previous code firstly gets the list of instance names from /INSTANCES ZNode and then gets the instance config one by one from /CONFIG/PARTICIPANT/INSTANCES ZNode. Whereas these two ZNodes may be inconsistent.
That's why we sometimes encounter flaky NPE when calling these APIs.

commit.message:
Fixed NPE bug for PartitionAwareOfflineRoutingTableBuilder (#2806)

PartitionAwareOfflineRoutingTableBuilder was caching the number of replicas
from the table config during the initialization and never updates the value
even if there was a change. This caused NPE when the broker attempts to compute
routing table after servers were added to table and rebalance was invoked.
This PR addresses this bug and also added the unit test to make sure the fix
resolves the issue.

commit.message:
[PINOT-4768] Handle exceptions when a table gets dropped while committing an LLC segment (#1275)

* [PINOT-4768] Handle exceptions when a table gets dropped while committing an LLC segment

We handle all exceptions inside the segment completion manager, and return a failed response.

Added unit test

* Changed exception and error string message

* Fixed the exception to be a RuntimeException instead of NPE

There are multiple points that call to get the segment metadata and they cannot handle null
for the metadata. One (normal) condition in which this can happen is:

  table getting dropped AND (segment completing OR validation manager auto-createing segments)

Other cases are manual edits of zknodes to remove metadata nodes (not expected)

Added an appropriate log message and turned the exception into RuntimeException instead of
NPE

commit.message:
[TE] harden alert scheduler against incomplete/incorrect alert configs (#1918)

The current implementation does not handle unchecked exceptions. A NPE can interrupt scheduler execution and kill the thread silently, e.g. if an incomplete or incorrect alertConfig is processed.

This PR hardens the scheduler and protects the top-level run() method. Furthermore, it gracefully degrades by skipping erroneous alertConfigs rather than terminating execution.

In the long run, TE's job and task scheduling framework requires a major reliability overhaul, e.g. by porting it to Apache Helix.

[PINOT 2095] Make TimeRetentionStrategy constructors consistent

TimeRetentionsStrategy could throw NPE for bad time unit values.
The behavior of the constructors and rest of the code was also
inconsistent in handling errors and negative values. This commit
fixes it.

commit.message:
Bug fixing for federated broker test.
1. fix logic for RealtimeColumnDataSource set range predicate as for
realtime dictionary, dictId is from 1 to dictionary size.
2. in MutableDictionaryReader, getString is also used for other data
type dictionary, so change it to toString().
3. fixing  offline ColumnDataSourceImpl would set filteredBitMap to null
in Range query, which actually should be an empty bitMap.
This is the root cause of DummyBlock get called.
4. fixing NPE in HelixExternalViewBasedTimeBoundaryService.
5. fixing time filter attching logic in BrokerRequestHandler for no
filter request.
6. changing attached time filters' ids to -1 and -2 to avoid potiential
duplicated.
